-- THAILAND PRESS-Thailand to help launch investment bank for Asia - The Nation
-- 
-- Wed Jul 16, 2014 08:27PM EDT
-- None



July 17 (Reuters) - Thailand has been invited by China to become one of the founding fathers of the Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank (AIIB), which is supported by this country's central bank, according to Bank of Thailand's Governor.       (http://bit.ly/1qgAZQY)    ----    NOTE: Reuters has not verified this story and does not vouch for its accuracy.   (Bangkok Newsroom; Editing by Subhranshu Sahu)  ((apornrath.phoonphongphiphat@thomsonreuters.com)(+66 2 648 9738)(Reuters Messaging: apornrath.phoonphongphiphat.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: THAILAND PRESS/AIIB

